@node Utilities
@section Utilities
@cindex utilities

The @samp{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}} package
builds and installs the following utilities:

@table @command
@item @value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}_mknod
This is a C-language program that can be used by startup scripts to create device nodes for the
@samp{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}} package.  This utility is normally installed in the @file{/usr/sbin}
directory.
See @manref{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}_mknod(8)} for more information.
@item @value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}
This is a @cite{RedHat}-style System V init script that is installed and used to start and stop the
@samp{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}} package.  Starting consists of creating SCTP device nodes using
@command{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}_mknod} and installing the @file{streams-sctp} and
@file{streams-tpiperf} modules in the running kernel.  This init script is normally installed in the
@file{/etc/init.d} directory.
@item @value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}.sh
This is a @cite{Debian}-style System V init script that is installed and used to start and stop the
@samp{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}} package in a similar fashion to the @command{@value{PACKAGE_TARNAME}}
script, but in the @cite{Debian} style.  This init script is normally installed in the
@file{/etc/rc.d/init.d} directory.
@end table

