@node NPI Interface Conformance
@section NPI Interface Conformance
@cindex NPI interface conformance

The Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) driver conforms to the @cite{Network Provider
Interface (NPI) Revision 2.0.0} as released by @cite{UNIX International}.  A copy of the original
document is available from @uref{http://www.openss7.org/docs/npi.pdf, The OpenSS7
Project Website}.
A reprint of the document specifying this version of the protocol is available as part of the
@samp{strxns} package available online in @uref{http://www.openss7.org/specs/npi.pdf,
PDF format}, or also in simple @uref{http://www.openss7.org/specs/npi.html, HTML
format}.

@node TPI Interface Conformance
@section TPI Interface Conformance
@cindex TPI interface conformance

The Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) driver conforms to the @cite{Transport Provider
Interface (TPI) Revision 2.0.0} as released by @cite{UNIX International}.  A copy of the original
document is available from @uref{http://www.openss7.org/docs/tpi.pdf, The OpenSS7
Project Website}.
A reprint of the document specifying this version of the protocol is available as part of the
@samp{strxnet} package available online in @uref{http://www.openss7.org/specs/tpi.pdf,
PDF format}, or also in simple @uref{http://www.openss7.org/specs/tpi.html, HTML
format}.

@node XTI Interface Conformance
@section XTI Interface Conformance
@cindex XTI interface conformance

The Stream Control Transmission Protocol (SCTP) driver conforms to the @cite{X/Open Transport
Interface/Transport Layer Interface (XTI/TLI) X/Open Networking Services (XNS) Revision 5.2} as
released by @cite{The OpenGroup}.  A copy of the original document is available from
@uref{http://www.opengroup.org/, The OpenGroup website}.
Reprints of the document are not available from The OpenSS7 Project website due to copyright
restrictions.  Similar information is available in the manual pages that accompany the
@samp{strxnet} package.  These can be viewed online starting at
@uref{http://www.openss7.org/man2html?3+xti, XTI/TLI manpage}.

